getting started with websockets 

blog -- https://medium.com/@phatdev/build-a-real-time-chat-application-with-websocket-socket-io-redis-and-docker-in-nestjs-499c2513c18


>> create a new nest project 
    >> nest new Project_name--skip-git 

>> delete unnecessary file like controllers and services 
>> create/generate a gateway application
    >> nest g gateway <folder_name> <app_name>           // it ll automatically generate a files and update the remaining files with
    >> install the nessary packages of websockets
        >> npm i --save @nestjs/websockets @nestjs/platform-socket.io



